File: City Power says there has already been a high number of unplanned outages in the past days. JOHANNESBURG - City Power says it expects more outages as the demand for electricity during the cold front increases. The power supplier says the high demand could overload the network as people continue to use illegal connections and heating appliances. READ: Cape Town to set up own electricity supply The system is under tremendous pressure due to the cold front and City Power is warning residents to use electricity sparingly. City Power says there has already been a high number of unplanned outages.